    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-27T16:51:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-27T16:51:00-05:00" n="828"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d828">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">684A.85/5–2754: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 828<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Israel</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d828fn1">Sent also to New York; repeated to Amman, London,
                        Paris, and Jerusalem; sent by air pouch to Ankara, Baghdad, Beirut, Cairo,
                        Damascus, Jidda, and Rome.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-05-27T17:51:00-04:00"
                            >May 27, 1954—5:51 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>818. UK Embassy reports French have decided join US–UK <hi rend="italic"
                        >démarche</hi> to Israel and Jordan re border measures and have urged two
                    tactical moves: (1) that Israel Government be informed of fact of <hi
                        rend="italic">démarche</hi> Amman re border measures and prospective similar
                    approach Israel this subject; (2) that reaction UNSYG be sought on measures
                        <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> could implement unilaterally. UK Foreign
                    Office has agreed these moves and instructed UK missions Tel Aviv and New York
                    proceed accordingly.</p>
                <p>Embassy should indicate to UK and French Embassies Tel Aviv that US associates
                    itself with UK–French advising Israel Government per (1) above with earnest hope
                        <gloss target="#t_IG1">IG</gloss> will keep matter confidential.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> will be advised shortly re joining in
                    UK–French approach UNSYG per (2) above.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF2">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
